com.davidsoergel.trees.dhtpn

Interface DoubleHierarchicalTypedProperties<I,J,K extends Comparable,V,C extends DoubleHierarchicalTypedProperties<I,J,K,V,C,H>,H extends HierarchicalTypedPropertyNode<K,V,H>>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    HierarchyNode<HierarchicalTypedPropertyNode<K,V,H>,C>, Iterable<C>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ExtendedDoubleHierarchicalTypedProperties<S,H>, ResultCollector, SerializableDoubleHierarchicalTypedProperties<S>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDoubleHierarchicalTypedProperties, AbstractSerializableDoubleHierarchicalTypedProperties

    public interface DoubleHierarchicalTypedProperties<I,J,K extends Comparable,V,C extends DoubleHierarchicalTypedProperties<I,J,K,V,C,H>,H extends HierarchicalTypedPropertyNode<K,V,H>>
extends HierarchyNode<HierarchicalTypedPropertyNode<K,V,H>,C>
    A data structure consisting of an outer tree, each node of which contains an inner tree.

    The outer tree has two IDs of types I and J.

    The inner tree is of type H. Each node of the inner tree contains a key-value pair of types K and V.

    The type C is a concrete type that implements this interface, indicating what types can be legally added as children.
